data.title: Princess Sophia Dorothea of Prussia
data.text:
Princess Sophia Dorothea of Prussia (Sophia Dorothea Marie; 25 January 1719 – 13 November 1765) was the ninth child and fifth daughter of Frederick William I of Prussia and Sophia Dorothea of Hanover. By marriage, she was a Margravine of Brandenburg-Schwedt.

Marriage[edit]

On 10 November 1734 in Potsdam, Sophia Dorothea married her distant cousin, Frederick William, Margrave of Brandenburg-Schwedt, son of Philip William, Margrave of Brandenburg-Schwedt, and Princess Johanna Charlotte of Anhalt-Dessau, daughter of John George II, Prince of Anhalt-Dessau.

Issue[edit]

Princess Friederike of Brandenburg-Schwedt (18 December 1736 – 9 March 1798) married Frederick II Eugene, Duke of Württemberg.

Princess Anna Elisabeth Louise of Brandenburg-Schwedt (22 April 1738 – 10 February 1820); married her uncle Prince Augustus Ferdinand of Prussia.

Prince Georg Philipp of Brandenburg-Schwedt (10 September 1741 – 28 April 1742)

Princess Philippine of Brandenburg-Schwedt (10 October 1745 – 1 May 1800) married Frederick II, Landgrave of Hesse-Kassel.

Prince Georg Philipp Wilhelm of Brandenburg-Schwedt (3 May 1749 – 13 August 1751)

Titles and styles[edit]

25 January 1719 - 10 November 1734 Her Royal Highness Princess Sophia Dorothea of Prussia.

10 November 1734 - 13 November 1765 Her Royal Highness The Margravine of Brandenburg-Schwedt.
